{
  "stem": "21786.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 15.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 59,
      "text": "And we had a teacher-- funnily enough, Eva had the same teacher as I had.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 60,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the only thing what I remember is a little bit being taught the Bible more or less as a historical document, and some basic prayers.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 61,
      "text": "We were singing something, the melodies I remembered.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 62,
      "text": "And we were torturing the poor man, I mean, to destruction.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 63,
      "text": "That I remember.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was called Savazska.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "S-A-V-A-Z-S-K-A synagogue-- a synagogue.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was a relatively nice building, built, I think, the turn of the century.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] it was attended, I would say by-- the congregation might have had, maybe I am exaggerating, but between 500 or 1,000 people.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I remember simply before one went into the synagogue, walking through the street and the-- a non-Jewish population simply watching the Jews walking in their fineries.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was about-- hm-- five blocks, six blocks from the place I lived.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was in Prague.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "At that point, it was Prague 12-- very close to this square where I-- where I went to my grammar school.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "His name was Rabbi Sicher, S-I-C-H-E-R.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he succeeded to leave [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] before the Nazi calamity, for Palestine.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he returned after the war to Prague.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was reinstated in some-- I think in a different function, for the Jewish population was decimated at that point.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he died in Prague, and he's buried in Prague.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The synagogue, I think, was changed into a school-- which, somehow, I don't mind, for it, at least, fulfills some purpose.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The Nazis did not destroy any of the Prague synagogues.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They used them for various purposes, usually as magazines or-- or storage.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But they were standing after the war.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
